This is a Java Maven project.

It is intended to be used by students in Trace Theory classes. It shows how
groups of graph productions can be executed block by block: a block starts,
all productions in that block finish, and only then the next block starts.

Requirements:

* JDK 26
* Maven 3.9 or newer, or the included Gradle Wrapper

Build with Maven:

    mvn clean package

Generate Javadoc with Maven:

    mvn javadoc:javadoc

Maven writes it to target/reports/apidocs. The package phase also attaches a
Javadoc JAR.

Run the Maven-built JAR:

    java -jar target/1DMeshParallel-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

Build with Gradle:

    ./gradlew clean build

Generate Javadoc with Gradle:

    ./gradlew javadoc

Gradle writes it to build/docs/javadoc. The build task also creates a Javadoc
JAR.

Run with Gradle:

    ./gradlew run

Run the Gradle-built JAR:

    java -jar build/libs/1DMeshParallel-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

For noncommercial use only.
